# A quick example workflow with nextflow in Kali Linux. 

curl -s https://get.nextflow.io | bash #Downloadas Nexflow, puts it in /home/kali

#This file is saved in *media/kali/Samsung/Users/Kai/Desktop/Nextflow script
#Focus on the run, pull, and drop commands: 

home/kali/nextflow # the location 
home/kali/nextflow run 

'Nextflow run can be used on a nextflow main.nf script or can be run directly from github repository. Let’s try this using a nextflow blast script developed by Iowa State’s Genome Informatic’s Facility (ISUGIF) by calling it directly from the Github repo.'

alias nextflow="/home/kali/nextflow" # make sure there is no white space around the "=", shortcuts the nextflow directory 
nextflow run isugifNF/blast --help


nextflow run isugifNF/blast -profile test #runs a test dataset from ISUGIF

EXECUTABLE OF THE ABOVE:

curl -s https://get.nextflow.io | bash
alias nextflow="/home/kali/nextflow"
nextflow run isugifNF/blast -profile test


